== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Keikō|Gekkyō Tennō]] 40th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:110 (number)|110]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ） – {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|qq=}} departed to subdue the eastern barbarians. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 2nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1855|ja|1855|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1855|qq=}} [[:en:November 11|November 11]] ） – The event of the {{Ansei Edo Earthquake|qq=}} is recorded, with heavy damage concentrated in downtown areas and over 7,000 fatalities. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1870|ja|1870|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1870|qq=}} [[:en:October 26|October 26]] ） – The Meiji government standardized military methods: the army adopted French models, and the navy British ones. == Births == * {{ill|Baireki|ja|Hōreki|1=Hōreki|2=ja|3=宝暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baireki|qq=}} 8th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1758|ja|1758|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1758|qq=}} [[:en:November 2|November 2]] ） – [[:en:Ryōkan|Ryōkan]] , a Sōtō Zen monk, poet, calligrapher († {{ill|1831|ja|1831|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1831|qq=}} ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Hōki|Hōki]] 6th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|775|ja|775|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/775|qq=}} [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ） – [[:en:Kibi no Makibi|Kibi Shinbi]] , a sinologist and court official (* [[:en:693 (number)|693]] ). * {{ill|Tenbun (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun (era)|qq=}} 22nd year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1553|ja|1553|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1553|qq=}} [[:en:November 7|November 7]] ） – [[:en:Yamazaki Sōkan|Yamazaki Sōkan]] , a renka master and haiku poet (* {{ill|1465|ja|1465|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1465|qq=}} ). * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 20th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1643|ja|1643|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1643|qq=}} [[:en:November 13|November 13]] ） – [[:en:Tenkai|Tenkai]] , a Tendai monk (* {{ill|1536|ja|1536|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1536|qq=}} ).
